library(readxl)
MPV_epidemiology_UW <- read_excel("MPV-epidemiology-UW.xlsx")
MPV_epidemiology_UW$WeekEnding <- as.Date(MPV_epidemiology_UW$WeekEnding, format="%Y-%m-%d")
MPV_epidemiology_UW$Totaltest <- as.numeric(MPV_epidemiology_UW$Totaltest)
MPV_epidemiology_UW$MPVpercpos <- as.numeric(MPV_epidemiology_UW$MPVpercpos)
library(ggplot2)

coeff <- 100
seasonality <- ggplot(MPV_epidemiology_UW, aes(x=WeekEnding)) +
    
    geom_line( aes(y=MPVpercpos), color="black") + 
    geom_line( aes(y=Totaltest / coeff), linetype = "dashed") +
    
    scale_y_continuous(
        # Features of the first axis
        name = "hMPV positive cases (%)",
        # Add a second axis and specify its features
        sec.axis = sec_axis(~.*coeff, name="Tested samples"),
        expand = c(0, 0)) +
    scale_x_date(date_breaks = "6 months", 
                 limits = as.Date(c('2018-1-1', '2025-2-1'), format = "%Y-%m-%d"),
                 date_labels="%b-%Y", expand = c(0, 0)) +
    theme_classic() +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90))

# Create date range
date_seq <- seq(as.Date("2018-01-01"), as.Date("2025-02-01"), by = "day")
x_numeric <- as.numeric(date_seq)

# Parameters
years <- 2018:2025
sd_days <- 25
peak_cases <- 8  # max cases at the peak of each curve

# Generate one normal curve per year, scaled to max = 8 % cases
all_curves <- lapply(years, function(y) {
  peak_date <- as.Date(paste0(y, "-03-25"))
  y_values <- dnorm(x_numeric, mean = as.numeric(peak_date), sd = sd_days)
  y_values <- y_values / max(y_values) * peak_cases  

  data.frame(
    date = date_seq,
    cases = y_values,
    year = as.character(y)
  )
})

# Combine into a single data frame
curves_df <- bind_rows(all_curves)

# Plot
expected <- ggplot(curves_df, aes(x = date, y = cases, group= year)) +
  geom_area(fill="steelblue", alpha=0.6) +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 8), breaks = 0:8, expand = c(0, 0)) +
  scale_x_date(date_labels = "%b-%Y", date_breaks = "6 months", expand = c(0, 0)) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90))
expected
